# Next.js Frontend Standards

## General Rules
- Always use targeted file edits. Never rewrite an entire file if only a small block needs to change.
- Do not install new npm dependencies without asking for explicit permission first.

## Code Style & Architecture
- **Framework:** Next.js App Router (TypeScript, Tailwind CSS).
- **Component Rules:** Keep components as React Server Components by default. 
- **Client Components:** Only add `'use client'` at the absolute top of the file if local state (`useState`, `useEffect`) or browser-only APIs are required.
- **Styling:** Use standard Tailwind utility classes. Avoid inline styles or custom CSS files.